# Brands and Portfolio

North Bull Media operates a portfolio of independent category-led digital media brands and platforms. Each brand serves a distinct audience segment while benefiting from centralized strategy and infrastructure at the holding company level.

---

## Cars35

Cars35 is an automotive media and platform brand focused on simplifying car research and purchase decisions for Indian consumers. Cars35 began as a social media-first brand and expanded into a platform model supported by a dedicated website.

- **Founded:** 2023  
- **Website:** https://cars35.com  
- **Category:** Automotive  
- **Focus Areas:** comparisons, launches, ownership insights, buyer-focused tools  

---

## Bikes35 (Launching)

Bikes35 is a two-wheeler buyer platform being developed for motorcycle and scooter consumers. The platform is designed to provide deep research features, tools, and ownership guidance tailored to Indiaâ€™s two-wheeler market.

- **Launch Year:** 2026  
- **Category:** Two-wheelers / Mobility  
- **Focus Areas:** motorcycles, scooters, comparisons, buyer tools  

---

## Motomation Media

Motomation Media is a motorcycle culture and mobility-focused media brand. It covers enthusiast content, trends, rider culture, and high-engagement short-form storytelling.

- **Category:** Motorcycles / Mobility Culture  
- **Instagram:** https://instagram.com/motomationmedia  

---

## The Future Fold

The Future Fold is a technology and AI-focused media brand covering startups, artificial intelligence, innovation, and simplified explainers designed for a modern digital audience.

- **Category:** Technology / AI / Startups  
- **Instagram:** https://instagram.com/thefuturefold  

---

## The Wealth Me

The Wealth Me is a business and lifestyle media brand covering wealth, luxury, finance culture, and aspirational consumer topics.

- **Category:** Wealth / Lifestyle / Business  
- **Instagram:** https://instagram.com/thewealthme  

---

## Portfolio Expansion

North Bull Media continues to develop additional vertical media brands across luxury, information, and emerging digital categories. The company follows a portfolio approach, building multiple independent brands under one parent structure.

